Wash and dry produce.

Using a #large drinking glass{} or #round cookie cutter{}, cut circles out of the
centers of @white bread{6%slices} (about a 3½-inch round per piece).

Trim and thinly slice @mini cucumber{1} into rounds.

Halve @orange{1}; slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons.

Halve @red grapes{2.25%oz} if desired.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @ground beef{10%oz} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}. Form into three patties (six patties for 6 servings), each
slightly wider than the bread rounds.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes}
per side.

In the last minute of cooking, top each patty with @cheddar cheese{½%cup} and
cover to melt cheese.

Transfer patties to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

Spread each bread round with @ketchup{1}. Top half the rounds with
cheesy patties and remaining bread rounds, ketchup sides down, to
form sliders.

To serve: Divide sliders between plates. Serve with @blue corn tortilla chips{1.5%oz},
cucumber rounds, orange slices, and grapes on the side.

To stash: Let sliders cool completely. Refrigerate sliders, tortilla chips,
cucumber rounds, orange slices, and grapes in separate containers and pack
as desired for lunch!

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.